    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style of carpets produced in the village of Sarāb, Iran; this is the name under which a particular phase and subvariety of Heriz carpet production was sold in the West. It is characterized by a light, rather bright color scheme.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
